media:group.media:title: Category Theory - Lecture 2 Part 1
media:group.media:description:
In this video we are talking about universal properties. We talk about initial and terminal objects, co/products, co/equalisers, and uniqueness up to unique isomorphism.
After this lecture I encouraged students to read 'Rethinking set theory' by Tom Leinster: https://arxiv.org/abs/1212.6543
